Russia and  Serbia  will sign an
accord tomorrow on the export of natural gas to the Balkan
nation through 2021, the government said today in an e-mailed
statement.  The agreement will envisage Serbia imports as much as five
billion cubic meters of gas a year, while prices will be
adjusted every year, said Dejan Milekovic, a spokesman for
